<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - OIL PAN, VIBRATION DAMPER, OIL
        PUMP, WATER PUMP, AND FRONT COVER - Installation - Oil Pan
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Oil Pan</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Do not apply excessive amounts of RTV sealant. Some could end up in the oil pick-up screen and
                    restrict oil flow. Such a restriction may result in engine damage. To avoid damaging the crankcase,
                    make sure no sealant gets in the oil pan bolt holes.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Wipe excess oil and foreign matter from all oil pan sealing surfaces. Use brake cleaner to
                thoroughly degrease all sealing surfaces before applying RTV sealant.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200534" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3338.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Apply RTV Sealant to the Crankcase Rails</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply RTV sealant to the bottom of the crankcase between and around the bolt holes to
                prevent leaks. Apply more at the front and rear mating surfaces.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install guide studs at two places on the crankcase to ensure proper oil pan alignment.
                Install the oil pan.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200535" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3526.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Oil Pan Bolt Hole Locations</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install mounting bolts finger tight. Remove the guide studs. Replace them with mounting
                bolts. Tighten all mounting bolts to the standard torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
